FT  07 JUN 93 / Iranian activist shot in Pakistan
An activist in the Iranian opposition Mujahideen Khalq movement was
assassinated in the Pakistani city of Karachi yesterday, a spokesman for the
movement said, Reuter reports. Mr Mohammad Hassan Arbab was shot in the back
while walking in the street near his home in the city, the spokesman said.
He blamed Iranian government agents.
A bystander was also shot and killed, he added.
